workflow.name: Extracts and organizes academic publications using GPT-4 Mini, Google Sheets, Gmail
workflow.description:
# Extract & Organize Academic Publications with GPT-4 Mini, Google Sheets & Gmail

**Author:** CSChin  
**Example Source:** https://www.ncl.ac.uk/singapore/staff/profile/chengchin.html#publications



## Overview

This automated workflow extracts, processes, and organizes academic publications from university staff profile pages using AI-powered extraction. Publications are automatically categorized by type and stored in organized Google Sheets while sending email notifications.

**Key Features:** AI extraction ‚Ä¢ Auto-categorization ‚Ä¢ Dual output (Sheets + Email) ‚Ä¢ Year-based sorting



## Target Audience

- **Academic Researchers** - Track publications across teams
- **University Administrators** - Manage faculty publication records  
- **Research Librarians** - Maintain institutional repositories
- **Department Heads** - Monitor research output
- **PhD Students** - Organize literature reviews



## Use Cases

1. **Automated Publication Tracking** - Monitor faculty research output
2. **Research Portfolio Management** - Maintain publication databases
3. **Citation Database Building** - Populate citation systems
4. **Department Reporting** - Generate organized reports by category/year
5. **Research Impact Analysis** - Track publication trends

**Source:** https://www.ncl.ac.uk/singapore/staff/profile/chengchin.html#publications

## Overview
Automated workflow extracts and organizes academic publications from university profiles using AI. Auto-categorizes and stores in Google Sheets with email notifications.

## Target Audience
Academic Researchers, University Administrators, Research Librarians, Department Heads, PhD Students

## Use Cases
Track faculty research output ‚Ä¢ Maintain publication databases ‚Ä¢ Generate reports by category/year

## Prerequisites
**Google Sheets** - API access, Spreadsheet IDs | **OpenAI API** - API key, GPT-4/3.5 access | **Gmail** - OAuth2 credentials (optional)

## Workflow Architecture
**Main Flow:** Form submission ‚Üí Fetch/parse HTML ‚Üí Split publications ‚Üí AI extracts data
**Path A:** Save to master sheet ‚Üí Route by type to category sheets (Journal, Conference, Book, Magazine, Preprints, Other)
**Path B:** Convert to CSV ‚Üí Send email

## Setup Instructions
**1. OpenAI:** Model: gpt-4-turbo, Temperature: 0.3, Prompt: Extract title, authors, year, type, venue, DOI, URL
**2. Google Sheets:** Append to master and category sheets
**3. Routing:** Route by publication type
**4. Email:** Subject: Publications Scraped | Body: Summary + CSV

## Customization
Add fields: Modify prompt ‚Ä¢ Change categories: Update routing ‚Ä¢ Multiple universities: Use URL patterns ‚Ä¢ AI models: GPT-4 or GPT-3.5 ‚Ä¢ Scheduling: Use Schedule Trigger
